File: The latest RMB/BER business confidence index shows that sentiment rebounded to 24 in the third quarter of this year from five points in the previous quarter. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's business confidence recovered from a record slump in the third quarter. The latest RMB/BER business confidence index shows that sentiment rebounded to 24 in the third quarter of this year from five points in the previous quarter. READ: South Africa's economy contracts by 51% in Q2 While the outcome is pleasing, sentiment remains heavily depressed; almost eight out of every ten business executives surveyed regard prevailing business conditions as unsatisfactory. The biggest contributors were manufacturing confidence and motor dealer confidence. Manufacturing confidence rebounded to 22 in the third quarter, up from six in the second quarter while motor dealer confidence jumped from two points to 16.